{"questionId":"19649","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following diagram shows the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>2</mn></math> and rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math>. The rectangle has a vertex at the origin <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></math>, a vertex on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-axis at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>, a vertex on the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis at the point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">T</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mfenced></math> and a vertex at point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow></mfenced></math> on the graph.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/fcdccef534b043a6d9577365baeda8eca8c55f07.png\"></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Let <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi></math> represent the perimeter of rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the dimensions of rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math> that has maximum perimeter and determine the value of the maximum perimeter.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>uses the axis of symmetry of a quadratic&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>forms&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>P</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the dimensions of rectangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math> of maximum perimeter are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their values of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the maximum perimeter is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>attempts to complete the square&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>M1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>substitutes their value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;into&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>(M1)</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mfenced><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the dimensions of rectangle&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ORST</mi></math>&nbsp;of maximum perimeter are&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp;by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>15</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>P</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>A1</strong></p>\n<p>so the maximum perimeter is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>17</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>[6 marks]</strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19649","referenceCode":"EXN.1.SL.TZ0.7b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the dimensions of rectangle ORST that has maximum perimeter and determine the value of the maximum perimeter.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}